Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.12,0:01:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In April 1943, with the Americans having captured Guadalcanal,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.86,0:01:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the Japanese were fiercely defending against them advancing along the Solomon Islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.88,0:02:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,lsoroku Yamamoto, Commander-in-Chief of the Allied Fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.46,0:02:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,flew from the base on Truck Island to Rabaul on the front line for a front-line inspection.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.81,0:02:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.56,0:02:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Salute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.21,0:02:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You see. It's a Japanese radio message.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The Combat Intelligence Department, which belongs to the United States Pacific Fleet Command in Hawaii,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.18,0:02:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is located in a top secret basement that can only be used by the cryptanalysis team.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.84,0:02:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All the radio messages of the Japanese Navy received from various parts of the South Pacific are collected here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.90,0:03:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and this electric cryptanalyzer was devised and developed by Major Thomas Dyer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.92,0:03:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,a leading expert in cryptographic analysis in the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.87,0:03:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It had been enhanced to the point where it could almost decipher the Japanese Navy's encrypted messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.55,0:03:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.52,0:03:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this? It's not like a Japanese sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.62,0:03:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if the machine broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.48,0:03:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.69,0:03:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Call Major Dier right away. It's urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.20,0:03:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Vengeance (Episode 18)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.86,0:04:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Major Dier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.36,0:04:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not a mechanical failure. The code of the Japanese Navy has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.40,0:04:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Has it changed completely?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.37,0:04:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.15,0:04:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, this machine is no longer useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.78,0:04:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to make a new decipherer. How many months will that take?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.28,0:04:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes half a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,However, cryptography does not always change completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.05,0:04:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyways, break this code.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.31,0:04:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.28,0:04:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you stay up all night, you must break this code.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.18,0:04:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.52,0:05:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How much can the Navy do if it comes to war with the United States and Britain?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.06,0:05:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a soldier. If I am told to do it, let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.90,0:05:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,For half a year or a year, we can plan as much as I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.82,0:05:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we cannot guarantee it after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.06,0:05:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.54,0:05:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That year is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.78,0:05:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.46,0:05:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.71,0:05:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I woke up after dreaming. I want to go to the beach, is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.20,0:05:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I will be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.98,0:06:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.43,0:06:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.24,0:06:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this feels better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.44,0:06:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's the sea where the war is going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.40,0:06:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been working in Rabaul all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.98,0:06:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I was in Bougainville three months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.15,0:06:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. It's the front line.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.99,0:06:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How was it, over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.66,0:06:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The Bougainville Reserves are unfortunately poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.57,0:06:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Rabaul any good?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.86,0:06:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.00,0:06:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to being in Rabaul, I can see the Commander-in-Chief of the Allied Fleet in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.64,0:06:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Just relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.84,0:06:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you glad I come to Rabaul so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.06,0:07:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The Chief is the guardian deity of the Imperial Japanese Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.82,0:07:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You are a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.48,0:07:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You exaggerate. I also drink alcohol and like gambling. Is there such a god?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.86,0:07:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you're God. You are right next to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.87,0:07:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for the people in Bougainville because they can't worship God directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.76,0:07:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Bougainville.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.10,0:07:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Bougainville.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.60,0:07:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel about carrying God?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.71,0:07:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I will have to pay for it. I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.34,0:08:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.63,0:08:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I solved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.80,0:08:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to stay up all night anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.74,0:08:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The code was broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.57,0:08:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese Navy did not change the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.02,0:08:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They just changed the random number table a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.41,0:08:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All we have to do is tell that to the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.05,0:08:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, that decryption machine can be used?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.62,0:08:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.70,0:08:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to Rabaul. I have to go to Bougainville.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.33,0:08:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Bougainville is 500kms from here. It's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.54,0:08:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The air superiority of this area is in our hands so far. It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.51,0:08:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the Japanese do not have complete air superiority.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.44,0:08:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know when the enemy planes will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.51,0:08:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but I think that the Commander-in-Chief should never leave the safe area.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.85,0:09:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Chief does that, then that will be when the Imperial Japanese Navy is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This theory is exactly what you guys say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.38,0:09:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.40,0:09:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto came all the way to Rabaul, but was it useful?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.78,0:09:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I can only make the soldiers guarding small islands around the Pacific think, "Hey, Yamamoto is here, lets do it well."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.10,0:09:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto shows his face here, then the front line for the Japanese forces isn't so terrifying. I want them to think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.89,0:09:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief. I understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.26,0:09:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Come out, come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.88,0:09:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.00,0:09:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's big news!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.12,0:09:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Connect to Lieutenant Colonel Layton. It's urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.18,0:10:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Colonel Layton enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.16,0:10:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Could Yamamoto make such a stupid mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.61,0:10:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it’s a trap, it’s too good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.52,0:10:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Just listen as you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.38,0:10:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the one who wrote such a message?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.53,0:10:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anyone who can describe the actions of the Commander-in-Chief of the Allied Fleet in such detail?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.92,0:10:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like sending an invitation to the enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.62,0:10:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the Chief know that I have flown from Bougainville.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.72,0:11:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief. Bougainville is absolutely okay as long as it is defended by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.33,0:11:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Please retrain from visiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.82,0:11:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean that I'll show up because I can't leave it to you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.25,0:11:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand, but why did you lay out that detailed schedule of the Chief's inspection?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.46,0:11:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What it this message is intercepted by the US?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.71,0:11:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Our code may have been broken, or they may not have been able to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.98,0:11:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It is usually undecipherable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.98,0:11:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot lose great joy in the unlikely event.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.85,0:11:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, can you believe this Japanese message?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.04,0:11:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the responsibility of Admiral Nimitz, Commander-in-Chief of the United States Pacific Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.30,0:11:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.30,0:11:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a top secret message from Dutch Harbor in Alaska.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.49,0:12:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.10,0:12:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On April 18th, Commander-in-Chief of the Allied Fleet Yamamoto will visit the island on the front line.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.00,0:12:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,6am, this must be Rabaul’s Japanese time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.00,0:12:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Depart Rabaul with six escort aircraft Zero fighters. 8am. Arrive at Bougainville.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.05,0:12:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It matches exactly with the message from the Japanese from Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.23,0:12:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We also caught this encrypted message in Alaska.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.56,0:12:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What was their intention in sending such a strong radio wave?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.19,0:12:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.08,0:12:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's the result of confidence that the US can't break their code.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.83,0:12:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We were given very difficult homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.52,0:13:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You already have the data that I have handed out. Ask questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.84,0:13:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There are few escort planes for Mr. Yamamoto, but there are also Zero fighters in Bougainville.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.16,0:13:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We only have P-38s. No matter how close we are to Yamamoto, we can't fly to Bougainville.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.73,0:13:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me answer. Bougainville certainly has Zero fighters, So hit Mr. Yamamoto before he lands on Bougainville.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.38,0:13:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Major Mitchell, it's time to explain your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.95,0:13:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can solve this homework, I will be the commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.94,0:13:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So here is my answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.50,0:13:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The target is Bougainville, about 600kms from our base.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.46,0:13:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing is how to fly so that the enemy does not see us coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.05,0:13:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we fly at a low altitude just above the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.80,0:13:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If Yamamoto, our key objective, does not fly as planned,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.32,0:13:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't it be possible to pass each other in the vast Pacific Ocean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.53,0:13:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. That is the most difficult point.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.44,0:13:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The distance from here to Bougainville is 600kms.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.98,0:14:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,500kms from Rabaul, where Mr. Yamamoto is, to Bougainville.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.24,0:14:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a difference of 100kms.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.79,0:14:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only one place in the South Pacific where the two lines meet most effectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.88,0:14:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How to find that one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.42,0:14:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.87,0:14:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.13,0:14:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Start one hour before Mr. Yamamoto and ambush him on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.38,0:14:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto is a man who always keeps his promises.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.26,0:14:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he really keep your promises? The attack on Pearl Harbor was a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.76,0:14:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that was a strategy to attack after the declaration of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.44,0:14:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, the people at the Japanese embassy In Washington made a mistake and the time was off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.20,0:14:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto struck Pearl Harbor at the promised time without knowing war had not been declared.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.06,0:14:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Make a note of the final decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.37,0:14:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,First proceed 133kms, 265 degrees directional. Speed 360kms, flight time 55 minutes, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.13,0:15:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, 144kms, 240 degrees orientation, 27 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.40,0:15:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Third, 200kms, 305 degrees orientation, 38 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.04,0:15:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If all goes well, we will definitely hit the enemy before 8 o'clock. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.98,0:15:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a wonderful answer to your homework, but Layton,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.61,0:15:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,no country killed an enemy Commander-In-Chief like this during World-War I.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.99,0:15:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. President, Yamamoto is was the planner for the undeclared attack on Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.00,0:15:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. This is fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.40,0:15:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Please make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.00,0:15:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There are only two days left.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Yamamoto is a regrettable man to bury.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.50,0:16:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief. I will take the first plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.51,0:16:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget to have the commander on the first plane. I am the commander today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.97,0:16:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.71,0:17:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The first plane has Chief Yamamoto, Major General Takada, and Deputy Secretary Fukusaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.72,0:18:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Staff Officer Ugaki and Aviation Staff Officer Muroi are on board the second aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.69,0:18:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese forces called this Mitsubishi G4 "Hamaki(sigar)",
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.49,0:18:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and the US forces called it "Betty" or "Writer".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.70,0:18:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The equipment was made extremely light to extend its cruising range,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.80,0:18:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which meant that it was flammable when shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.09,0:18:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We lost one more. 16 aircraft left.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.43,0:18:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever. If the enemy Yamato has a soul, there is also a Yankee soul here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.60,0:18:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, I should meet Gentleman Yamamoto soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.69,0:18:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief. 10 minutes before landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.00,0:19:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Chief. It's time to prepare for landing,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.20,0:19:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.63,0:19:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I laugh when I meet the soldiers for the first time?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.78,0:19:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should I be dignified?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.60,0:19:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if I came a little too early.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.76,0:19:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it I'll use the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.46,0:19:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy plane found. 11 o'clock direction. Altitude 2000.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Send to all aircraft. Discovered Betty. Drop the spare tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.47,0:20:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It enemy aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.92,0:20:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't panic, the base is close.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.72,0:20:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It is an enemy aircraft!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.59,0:20:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.94,0:20:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Protect the Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.79,0:20:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one is Yamamoto on? Anyway, I can shoot both.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.00,0:20:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the soul of Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.60,0:20:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.48,0:20:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Recover!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Betty
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.27,0:21:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.54,0:21:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.36,0:21:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.53,0:21:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, please hold on firmly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.34,0:22:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.89,0:22:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.39,0:22:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't lose sight of the Chief's plane. It was attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.42,0:22:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Mitchell. Message to all aircraft. Both Bettys fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.05,0:22:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We have served our purpose. Run away if you want a medal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.74,0:23:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were on the first plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.06,0:23:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When a man who tried to avoid the war ironically has to take command of the battle, he fights like a lion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.20,0:23:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably knew his destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.53,0:23:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,lsoroku Yamamoto's death is by no means a careless death. By dying, he believed in those who followed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.30,0:23:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This sad act taught us that in order to win the battle, we must know our enemies well.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.19,0:23:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Even today, the more accurate information you have, the better you can make the decisions to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.56,0:23:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The death of Isoroku Yamamoto eventually led to the setting sun of the Japanese Empire.
